136
00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:37.810
Different house scarves.

137
00:08:37.810 --> 00:08:38.810
Lego.

138
00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:40.779
Collectors edition sets of the books and movies.

139
00:08:40.779 --> 00:08:41.779
Over-priced wands.

140
00:08:41.779 --> 00:08:45.520
I was even saving up to pay an exorbitant
amount of money for tickets to see the Cursed

141
00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:49.020
Child play before I read it and realized it
was horrible.

142
00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:52.720
But it wasn’t written by Rowling, so that
explained everything!

143
00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:57.550
As far as I was concerned everything she touched
was gold.

144
00:08:57.550 --> 00:09:02.870
And then… things started to rust.

145
00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:06.920
PART TWO: The Chamber of Anger

146
00:09:06.920 --> 00:09:08.020
First came The Crimes of Grindlewald.

147
00:09:08.020 --> 00:09:12.810
I don’t think I’ve ever given a movie
so much leeway.

148
00:09:12.810 --> 00:09:17.920
Leading up to the release I, and many other
people, were incredibly excited to finally

149
00:09:17.920 --> 00:09:22.911
