751
00:47:56.430 --> 00:48:01.279
She hasn’t been the one keeping the series
alive with countless theory videos and head

752
00:48:01.279 --> 00:48:04.180
canon explanations across the internet.

753
00:48:04.180 --> 00:48:06.249
She just confirms them sometimes.

754
00:48:06.249 --> 00:48:10.789
And when she comes up with her own, its about
Wizards crapping on the ground and magicking

755
00:48:10.789 --> 00:48:12.039
it away with their wand.

756
00:48:12.039 --> 00:48:15.540
The fans are the people who have kept this
brand alive since the books finished their

757
00:48:15.540 --> 00:48:23.960
run in 2007, the year I graduated from high
school, and the final film was released in

758
00:48:23.960 --> 00:48:24.960
2011.

759
00:48:24.960 --> 00:48:29.189
Long before Rowling officially launched Pottermore
in 2015, (everything before then was considered

760
00:48:29.189 --> 00:48:34.339
a beta), fans had been doing the hard work
of keeping their favourite characters alive.

761
00:48:34.339 --> 00:48:36.829
Fans took ownership of the the characters.

762
00:48:36.829 --> 00:48:40.729
Fan fiction communities for Harry Potter had
always been popular, but they really took

763
00:48:40.729 --> 00:48:43.449
